A Parent–Child Learning Journey

A home-based learning project built through daily interaction, play, and curiosity

Why This Project Was Created

These games were built for my son, Howie, inspired by his natural curiosity, recognising words, counting everyday objects, and exploring sounds through play.

Rather than following a rigid curriculum, I focused on his interests and pace, designing activities to build confidence before speed. Learning grows best through engagement, persistence, and joy.

These games are shared freely, in the hope of helping other children experience learning as something positive, accessible, and joyful, no matter their background.

Explore Learning Games

Learning Philosophy & Approach

Young children learn best through play, encouragement, and genuine connection. Every activity is built on listening and responding to the child's pace.

Core Principles

No Pressure, No Competition

No timers, no scores, no comparison. Learning happens at the child's own pace.

Encouragement & Reflection

Every attempt is valued. We celebrate effort and curiosity, then reflect on what we learned.

Bilingual Exposure

Chinese and English are woven naturally into daily activities, without separation.

Early Readiness Focused

Activities build phonemic awareness, number sense, patterns, and social confidence.
